OL,3,CSon calls for assisted dying law
OL,4,Cchange after father left 'beaten husk
OL,5,Cof a man'
OL,7,FPat Malone told ITV News' Bob Cruwys
OL,8,Fhis father was left "without any
OL,9,Fdignity" after being diagnosed with
OL,10,Fterminal cancer.
OL,12,FA man whose father had terminal cancer
OL,13,Fand pleaded for someone "to put poison
OL,14,Fin his water" has voiced his support
OL,15,Ffor legalising assisted dying.
OL,17,FPat Malone, from Bodmin, Cornwall,
OL,18,Fsaid his father endured "appalling
OL,19,Fpain that couldn't be relieved" in the
OL,20,Fweeks leading up to his death from
OL,21,Fcancer in the 1990s.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/9
