OL,3,CSon calls for assisted dying law
OL,4,Cchange after father left 'beaten husk
OL,5,Cof a man'
OL,7,FMr Malone is urging MPs to support the
OL,8,Flegalisation of assisted dying in
OL,9,FEngland and Wales, and said he
OL,10,Fbelieves the current law is "out of
OL,11,Fdate".
OL,13,F"It belongs in the last century and it
OL,14,Fneeds to be consigned to the last
OL,15,Fcentury," he said. "I think in memory
OL,16,Fof my siblings and my father a law
OL,17,Fchange cannot come soon enough."
OL,19,FOpponents of assisted dying say that
OL,20,Flegalisation could put pressure on
OL,21,Fmany to end their lives.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
